<PageTitle>About - Snow Day Predictor</PageTitle>

<div class="container">
    <div class="main-content">
        <h1>About Snow Day Predictor</h1>

        <p>Snow Day Predictor helps you estimate the likelihood of school closures or delays due to winter weather.</p>

        <h3>How It Works</h3>
        <p>Our algorithm analyzes weather forecasts from the National Weather Service and calculates snow day probabilities based on:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Temperature:</strong> Below-freezing conditions increase the chance of snow accumulation</li>
            <li><strong>Precipitation Type:</strong> Snow, sleet, and freezing rain predictions</li>
            <li><strong>Precipitation Probability:</strong> Higher chances mean more likely accumulation</li>
            <li><strong>Forecast Severity:</strong> Keywords like "heavy snow" or "blizzard" boost probabilities</li>
            <li><strong>Timing:</strong> Overnight and early morning conditions are weighted more heavily</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Data Sources</h3>
        <p>Weather data is provided by:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>National Weather Service (NOAA):</strong> Official forecast data</li>
            <li><strong>Zippopotam.us:</strong> ZIP code to city name lookup</li>
            <li><strong>OpenStreetMap Nominatim:</strong> Geocoding services</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Disclaimer</h3>
        <p class="text-muted">
            Snow Day Predictor is for informational and entertainment purposes only.
            Actual school closures depend on many factors including local policies, road conditions,
            and administrator decisions. Always check official sources for school closure announcements.
        </p>

        <h3>Privacy</h3>
        <p>
            Your saved locations are stored locally in your browser. No personal data is sent to external servers
            except for public weather API requests. Location data (if you choose to share it) is only used to
            fetch weather forecasts and is not stored or transmitted elsewhere.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-4">
            <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">← Back to Forecast</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

